caption: Great Job, Graham for reinterpreting the run of the mill, boring CHICKEN & WAFFLES.  👍👍 Excellent portion for price with zero filler.  Salty pork belly is a contrast to sweet maple aioli.  I like this crunchy Waffle Cone better than the doughy plain waffle.  No worries, CHICKEN & WAFFLE looks different but, TASTE the same.  Charming SYLWIA is classy.
Good food, good drinks, great service, and an amazing back patio!

I had a similar experience to one of the earlier reviewers, Kate, below.  I was excited to finally try Graham’s newest restaurant upon its opening month. Our party of 3 shared half a dozen plates, bottle of wine, and dessert, and weren’t wowed by any of them.  All were incredibly salty and underwhelming. In fact, the only dish we did love was the fried beet spirals, which is embarrassingly easy to make. We tried the king crab, which is literally half or third of a leg no more than 3” long, plated with some sauce for $20.  There’s a reason why you can get a table here the night of on Friday or Saturday. Get a cocktail if you must but then walk over for dinner at Maude’s, Elske, Avec, Lena Brava, etc. for a fulfilling dining experience.

This was a Capital one event to launch tastemaker Chicago and a collaboration between Gram Elliott (a two Michelin star Chef) and his partner with Gideon sweet. They created a unique, never before seen 5 course meal with an additional surprise of foie gras. All pairings were well thought out! An Incredible experience! I would recommend his restaurant in a heartbeat! GREAT GOURMET FOOD!!!!!

The server was great. The food was not. Most of the plates looked pretty but tasted either okay or less than okay. A friend and I each had three plates and were not wowed by any of them. Those three plates cost more than $50...it just wasn't worth it.
Lack luster food

First of all, the lobsters were too fishy and smells bad. The waitress said that the meetball is her favourite its sucks 4 small meatballs with bechamel sauce no seasoning at all. The only dishes we loved that day was the spiral potatoes and the avocado humus.  Iam really a fan of Graham Elliot but i was shocked that this is the quality of food on his restaurant.
Great cocktails and bartender! Fun place :-) yummy appetizer too
Amazing outdoor seating in a vivid neighborhood. Delicious tapas style food. You can trust the servers for excellent recommendations.
Chef Elliott rocks the joint with great music and ambience and solid food to keep patrons coming back for more
King crab, amazing!
Great beer selection.  We had already eaten but menu looked yummy.
Great food and atmosphere! Definitely will return

The food is soooooo good!!! We only ordered off the appetizer list and were full to contentment. They are extremely accommodating and take into account all food sensitivity and allergies.  We had the seadoned Tofu ( I don't usually like but delish), the cauliflower, the crispy potatoes, the avocado hummus, and the beignets. Everything was heavenly. To top it off, my friend is dairy free gluten free and they had a special dessert not on the menu that was reserved solely for her peeps 😁😁😁. Highly recommended!!!

I like Gideon Sweet. I've gone a couple times now for appetizers and cocktails which are great. They seem to have a good bar program here. My plan is to return this summer to experience the outside patio and dinner!
Creative dishes, but many were too salty or overseasoned. Desserts we're good tho.
Really great service, very knowledgeable of the menu. The cauliflower is a must!

Food was tiny and meh, service was meh, furnishings were laughably cheap, slow service, wine/cocktails were good. Spent $150 on 6 courses and 4 drinks and then went across the street to Maude's Liquor Bar and split a burger because we were still hungry...
GE's done it again! All around great service, food, and atmosphere.

I honest hate to give low reviews,  but the food just isn't there. The waitor suggested 6-8 plates to share for my date and I, but how do you share a 3in tostada? Or a single meatball and a 1/4 papadum? Food was pretty bland and we ended up getting pizza around the corner.
Walked in with low expectations. However, the dishes were great and our server was on point. The beignet really topped off the meal
Good food and service was great. A bit surprised it wasn't busier on the evening we went.
Food and service that's outstanding.  Unique plates that are delicious and just great fun to enjoy.

I hate giving it three stars. I'm a huge fan of Graham Elliot. I loved GE Bistro. I wanted to love this...but the food just isn't there. It tasted good, it was fine...but nothing wow, nothing made us want more. The cocktail menu for being cocktail forward needed more depth. We only spent $140, but didn't walk away thinking we would return soon...and I hate saying that. I know Graham's genius gos far beyond this

New place in the West loop area that is still working out some kinks. The cocktails were solid and well crafted. However several items we ordered were not available and that wasn't made very clear to us when we ordered. I imagine they'll improve as time goes on

The food at Gideon Sweet is inspired and fun. The Naschen-style dining concept is great, and provided many pleasant surprises in addition to the items we ordered from the menu. Small plates work well, and provided the opportunity to try a wide sampling of the many wonderful creations on offer. The art that adorns the space is a treat and the music playing at just the right volume was a great accompaniment to our experience.
Outstanding, food and drink combinations were spot on, our server Jessica was excellent and Tim the GM took care of all our needs
Great place for apps and small plates.   Graham Elliot shines!
Loved the small plates and cocktails. I can't wait to go back and try what I missed on the menu. Great place to bring someone you want to impress without breaking the bank.

The food and drinks were excellent.  Seriously, go for the sweetbreads and pig's ear.  However, the service was sub part to say the very least.  Admittedly, we came on opening night, so a few hiccups in service were bound to happen.   But we ended up having to wait 30 minutes after our plates were cleared, and our cocktails were gone before somebody asked us if we needed anything else.  Totally would have gone for the Japanese Cheesecake, but the moment kind-of passed.  I'll definitely be back to see how things progress.  But I was more than a bit annoyed when I left, which is never how you want to feel after dinner.

Our service was fantastic, cocktails on point and the food was just right. Atmosphere was vibrant, casual but still warm. Since it’s so close to opening, I was prepared for some hiccups but nothing materialized. So happy we went there for dinner last night.

One of the best dining experiences of my life.  Food was elegant and portioned in a pinxtos manner. Drinks are elegant as well as perfectly currated. Service is dialed-in and felt like family. Ambience is unique yet casual. The management has a local following because everything they touch turns to gold.  Don't be a fool - go here and eat right away.
Now closed for renovations and a relaunch under a new name but was a great place for some food and drinks. Great service from the staff.

Made a reservation for tonight, and showed up, and the restaurant is under construction??? How do you accept a reservation when your not even open. Took time off of work to come enjoy a fab meal, and found that it was closed. Very disappointed. Won't be returning...
Horrible that this restaurant allows a 3rd party to accept reservations on line and they aren't even open.  Never again.
Great food. Been there twice and got something different both times.

We went there as a party if 4. There are only around 25 tables in the whole place . We waited over an hour to get any food and our waiter was not handling anything very well. He was emotional and made us feel like we were bothering him every time we asked about the food. Nothing was brought out  to hold us over till we got our meals. Once we got our food it was delicious. The service.....not so much. 300$ later, I don't think we would go back.
You must try the ravioli!!
Food is second to none. Graham will come say hello to guests and take photos. We found a Groupon for here and ended up saving us some money. High recommend going here.

Great food.  Great atmosphere. Great times. My wife and I dined here and split 3 "plates."  The sweet pea risotto, the rabbit schnitzel, and the filet stroganoff. We also had dessert. She got the root beer float, I got the banana split.  We also had cocktails.  Everything was cooked to perfection.  And our night was made perfect with Graham Elliot visiting our table and taking pictures!  When it was all said and done, we spent $110.  A little steep for some perhaps, but well worth a great night on the town.

We were very disappointed by our experience.  The food was mediocre and the seating was uncomfortable.  The leg of lamb was actually four silver dollar sized slices of nondescript lamb.  The burger would have been better without the sweet onion marmalade. After having enjoyed Girl and the Goat earlier this year, we were excited to visit this restaurant because we thought it would been on par with Girl and the Goat.  It fell way short.  We would have been better off going to an old standby like Wildfire which produces consistent food.  We read other negative reviews and thought that the diners were being overly critical.  We were wrong.

Don't skip the brussel sprouts, they're delicious.  We also enjoyed the chicken liver mousse and the scallops but the standout dishes were the short rib stroganoff and a blast from my childhood the coke float.

Me and my family came from Miami just to eat here and the whole experience was FANTASTIC,  some people said it is over priced ,but everyone must understand Graham  Elliot is a world class chef. On my next visit this place is a "must". We also met Graham and he was so friendly and nice with everyone and accessible Highly recommended.
Everything we had was FANTASTIC. Great atmosphere and friendly staff made it all a great experience. Going back again soon!

This was the saltiest food I have ever had the misfortune of ordering. The waiter didn't check back with us and acted like he was too busy to answer any questions.    We ordered the milk and honey which was the most edible of anything we had tonight but still not great.  Then we had  the cheddar risotto which was the worst risotto I've ever had.  Then I had the winter greens and my friend ordered the beef stroganoff.  The winter greens were like a salt lick for a deer and the stroganoff was just a big hunk of beef with one mushroom.  We couldn't wait to leave.
Good but overpriced food.
Great food

Absolutely fantastic. We drove in from Aurora and this place made it worth the drive. First off, we made a reservation through Open Table for 5 people. I'd recommend if you make a reservation for more than 4 that you call instead. We had to make the reservation for 10pm and the restaurant called to confirm and offered an earlier time which we took. Most of the tables are "4 person tables" but due to the bench seating can easily accommodate a 5th if the place isn't packed. The hostess can easily make that determination, but open table can't so it tells you all the large tables are booked, etc. So if open table gives you weird times, just call and double check.  The food was out of this world and the restaurant was casual and laid-back while still keeping an upscale feel. You could wear anything from jeans to cocktail attire and feel comfortable. The bartender was great, he made some custom drinks for a few people in our party. The service was excellent, our waiter was knowledgeable, friendly and prompt. On top of all that, it was priced very reasonably for the quality food that we ordered. They have a tasting/pre fix option (if one person gets that, everyone at the table has too) and an a la carte option. They suggest getting one item from each section of the menu to get the full experience, but you could easily have a light meal and only pick one or two options. The oysters and salmon tartare were phenomenal. We will definitely be going back to g.e.b. soon!
Awesome

We decided on GEB since The Girl and The Goat was packed and the next available table would easily be a 3 hour wait. Boy am I glad we did!  It was three of us so, we decided to order 3 different appetizers and share, this way we can try more plates. All three plates were delicious: the burrata, the octopus and the foie gras. I would say my least favorite was the octopus, but only because I've had, either similar or as good octopuses at  other restaurants.  For entrees we decided on an entree each: Scallops, Salmon and OH! the Porchetta <-- this was A-MA-ZING! They were all cooked to perfection.  My only regret was the 'polenta' my scallops came with, it was tasteless and the texture was not my favorite.  For dessert we shared one: the key lime pie. It was absolute  delicous-goodness!

OK, first things first. I have never had such great tasting food as I had here at GEB (Graham Elliot Bistro).  To top it off, Graham Elliot was at the restaurant that night and we got to chat with him and take a few pictures. If you do not know who Graham Elliot is, he is one of the three judges of the popular reality show MasterChef.  So my wife and I were in Chicago for the Labor day weekend and even before we took off, we had made a reservation for GEB.  We got our table promptly once we were at the restaurant and were treated with top notch service. We got complimentary popcorn which was really out of the world. They were spiced perfectly and we all just couldnt stop until the whole plate was clean.  For drinks, I got strawberry lemonade which was extremely tasty and fresh.  For our main course, I got Lamb trio which they made vegetarian with Chickpeas paste and it was amazing. Chickpea paste was so smooth that it melted in the mouth and tasted a bit like cheese. Even the veggies and the green beans that came with it were very flavorful. We also got the lobster risotto (without the lobster) and grilled eggplant and each dish was out of the world.  We had read good things about the desserts so we decided to order three different ones to try them out. We got the Creme brûlée, Banana Split and deconstructed key lime pie. Trust me, we have never had such good desserts before. The desserts were not overly sweet but were just perfect.  Tip: Make sure you have the desserts here or your visit to GEB wont be worth.  Parking might not be that easy depending on when you go so look for street parking around the block or get a valet.

Ok to be fair I did not eat here but the atmosphere was so weird that I am glad I only stayed for one drink. And so was my wallet. It was almost $30 for two drinks. Now, don't get me wrong, I have no problem spending a pretty penny on a great drink but these were pretty average. We had intended to just sit at the bar for a drink and move on but as soon as we walked in we realized there were no seats at the bar so we were forced to sit at a table. Weird.

Coming to this restaurant is truly a beautiful experience! The waitstaff were very helpful and knowledgeable, and I loved being able to interact with the chefs! Both the waitstaff and the chefs checked up on me and my date constantly throughout the night to make sure that we were having a great time, and that's a kind of friendly and appreciative type of customer service that can't be obtained anywhere else. And getting the delicious food and wine that we received, as well as being in a wonderfully designed atmosphere was even more of a highlight to a fantastic night.

G.E.B. is one of those places that was on my short list, but somehow every time I overlooked it.  Finally I went here for a GNO.  I have to say, the staff here is great.  The hostess was super friendly, bartender excellent and our server read us like a book.  We loved it.  The food was excellent as well.  We had the mixed green salad, risotto, and the white fish.  The salad was pretty standard.  I have to say, the risotto was decadent.  Creamy, cheesy, bacony, herb-y...it was excellent...and crazy only $11???  How is that even possible?!  The white fish was cooked to perfection.  There was a simple crust and the inside flaked off like butter.  The sauce was dill-like and just made a perfect bite with the fish and potatoes.  To end the meal, we had to get the banana split.  It was FAN-FREAKING-TASTIC!  Salty, sweet, crunchy and aesthetically pleasing as well.  The scene was great.  It was a perfect bistro setting.  Loud, bustling, but not too much.  The kitchen was open as well.  I like that new concept that everyone and their brother is doing in the city.  Overall, I really enjoyed GEB.  The staff, food, setting were all great.  I would definitely go back.

Brunch: Low key diner-like spot from Graham Elliott featuring creative takes on heavier  items, like a burger (with gruyere fondue), veggie flatbread (with ricotta), biscuits and gravy (with poached egg), oatmeal (with dates and pecans) and seasonal pumpkin bread (with salted butter) - Visited on: November 24, 2012
Fantastic meal at GEB.  Looking forward to getting there again soon.....especially the homemade pasta....
